rna Kostash, Peter Stevens, Aritha van Herk, and Christopher Wiseman. The collection will naturally be of interest to any student of Canadian literature, but the essays also forcefully address, both explicitly and implicitly, the question of a nationalism of the arts, an issue of great importance to performers and critics in many fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors and readersvCongresses. 0aAuthors and readersxCongresses. 0aCanadian literaturexCongressesxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aCanadian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aLittérature canadiennex20e siècle. 0aReader-response criticismxCongressesxCanada. 0aReader-response criticismzCanadavCongresses. 0aÉcrivains et lecteursxCanadaxConference papers and proceedingsxCriticism, interpretation, etc. 4aLiterary Criticism: Canadian Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aBlodgett, E.D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrault, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDansereau, Estelle, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGiguère, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, D. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKostash, Myrna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStevens, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiseman, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan Herk, Aritha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eB